begin
reserve a for Integer;
reserve b for Integer;
theorem
( a gcd b ) = ( ( abs a ) gcd ( abs b ) )
proof
A1: (( abs b ) = b or ( abs b ) = ( - b )) by ABSVALUE:1;
A2: (( abs a ) = a or ( abs a ) = ( - a )) by ABSVALUE:1;
A3:now
let m being Integer;
assume (m divides ( abs a ) & m divides ( abs b ));
then (m divides a & m divides b) by A2,A1,CKB23:1;
hence m divides ( a gcd b ) by CKB16:def 1;
end;
( a gcd b ) divides b by CKB16:def 1;
then A4: ( a gcd b ) divides ( abs b ) by A1,CKB23:1;
( a gcd b ) divides a by CKB16:def 1;
then ( a gcd b ) divides ( abs a ) by A2,CKB23:1;
hence thesis by A4,A3,CKB16:def 1;
end;
